    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{-22, 22, 11, -19, 8, 7\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the sample mean ($\\bar{x}$)\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{-22 + 22 + 11 - 19 + 8 + 7}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{1}{6} = 0.1667\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared deviations from the mean\n\n$$\n(-22 - 0.1667)^2 = (-22.1667)^2 = 491.2667\n$$\n$$\n(22 - 0.1667)^2 = (21.8333)^2 = 476.4444\n$$\n$$\n(11 - 0.1667)^2 = (10.8333)^2 = 117.3611\n$$\n$$\n(-19 - 0.1667)^2 = (-19.1667)^2 = 367.2667\n$$\n$$\n(8 - 0.1667)^2 = (7.8333)^2 = 61.3556\n$$\n$$\n(7 - 0.1667)^2 = (6.8333)^2 = 46.6944\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared deviations\n\n$$\n\\text{Sum} = 491.2667 + 476.4444 + 117.3611 + 367.2667 + 61.3556 + 46.6944 = 1450.5875\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1$ (sample variance formula)\n\n$$\ns^2 = \\frac{1450.5875}{6 - 1} = \\frac{1450.5875}{5} = 290"
